cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper discusses location privacy in Cognitive Radio Networks (CRNs) and proposes a new scheme for cooperative spectrum sensing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves wireless communication and network optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes a voting-based sensing approach, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
